***LIST***.
Two middle schools serve portions of Willis:
***LIST***.
All of the city is zoned to Willis High School in Unincorporated Montgomery County.
Portions of the city used to be zoned to Turner Elementary School until the attendance zoned changed for the 2006–2007 school year, rezoning the portion to Hardy Elementary School .
========,3,Colleges and universities.
Lone Star College (originally the North Harris Montgomery Community College District) serves the community.
The territory in Willis ISD joined the community college district in 1996.
The system operates the Fairbanks Center in unincorporated Harris County; Fairbanks Center is a part of Lone Star College–CyFair.
